episodes.title: Exit 9B
episodes.plot: When everyone is brainwashed and the park is destroyed, Mordecai and Rigby have to bring everyone back their old selves so they can prevent a highway from being built over the park.

episodes.title: Starter Pack
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to get Muscleman to stop pranking Thomas when they realize that his pranks are getting out of hand.

episodes.title: Terror Tales of the Park II
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

episodes.title: Pie Contest
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby take over the duty of judging the Park's Pie Contest, but realize that the job isn't all that easy when they find out that they have to pick a winner.

episodes.title: 150-Piece Kit
episodes.plot: Benson tries to assemble a 150-piece drum kit to prove that he performed a famous drum solo for a well-known rock band.

episodes.title: Bald Spot
episodes.plot: When Muscle Man notices a bald spot on his head, he tries to cover it to keep Starla from seeing it at their date.

episodes.title: Guy's Night
episodes.plot: Pops tries to complete the Milk Challenge to prove that he is worthy of becoming one of the guys.

episodes.title: One Pull Up
episodes.plot: Rigby must perform a single pull-up to avoid being fired on the grounds of poor personal fitness.

episodes.title: The Christmas Special
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby have to destroy a gift for Santa, to save Christmas.

episodes.title: TGI Tuesday
episodes.plot: Margaret is transferring to another college, so Mordecai, Rigby and Eileen plan a going-away party at the park's abandoned ballroom, still haunted by its past hosts.

episodes.title: Firework Run
episodes.plot: Muscle Man, Mordecai, Rigby, and High five ghost blow up the fourth of July fireworks and are forced to drive to get new ones.

episodes.title: The Longest Weekend
episodes.plot: To prove their love for each other, Muscleman and Starla plan to stay away from each other for one weekend.

episodes.title: Sandwich of Death
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby buy a potentially deadly sandwich at a restaurant, but when Benson falls ill after he eats it himself, they must set out to find the cure before he dies.

episodes.title: Ace Balthazar Lives
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby want to reunite a famous band when they think the lead singer, who was presumably dead, is alive and living in the park.

episodes.title: Do or Diaper
episodes.plot: Muscle Man bets Mordecai that if he doesn't kiss Margaret by Friday at midnight, he will have to wear a diaper for a week.

episodes.title: Quips
episodes.plot: Skips has to tell is cousin, Quips, to stop telling bad jokes when he comes to visit.

episodes.title: Caveman
episodes.plot: While camping out in a cave, Mordecai and Rigby accidentally melt a caveman frozen in a block of ice. When they try to keep him, Benson requires that they make him more civilized.

episodes.title: That's My Television
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby help their favorite '80s sitcom star, RGB2, escape from the studio lot and into the mountains to get out of a contract that has trapped him into staying on the show.

episodes.title: A Bunch of Full Grown Geese
episodes.plot: When the park becomes invaded by vicious territorial geese, Mordecai and Rigby seek the help of the baby ducks to get rid of them.

episodes.title: Fool Me Twice
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to get on a Japanese Game Show so they can win the grand mystery prize.

episodes.title: Limousine Lunchtime
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby accidentally coat the interior of Mr. Maellard's limousine in meatball sub.

episodes.title: Picking Up Margaret
episodes.plot: When Mordecai volunteers to drive Margaret to the airport, he tries to convince Benson to let him use his car.

episodes.title: K.I.L.I.T. Radio
episodes.plot: Muscleman, Mordecai and Rigby help "Donny G", a famous D.J. take back over the corrupt local radio station so Muscleman can play his song he wrote for Starla on the radio.

episodes.title: Carter and Briggs
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby enter a vehicular doughnut contest to win guest spots on their favorite police procedural TV show.

episodes.title: Skips' Stress
episodes.plot: Skips faces dire consequences when he passes up a day off to reduce his deadly amount of stress.

episodes.title: Cool Cubed
episodes.plot: When Thomas is incapacitated by a dangerously cold slushie flavor, Mordecai and Rigby must enter his brain to prevent the drink from killing him.

episodes.title: Trailer Trashed
episodes.plot: A health inspector threatens to shut down the park if sanitary conditions inside Muscle Man's trailer are not improved.

episodes.title: Meteor Moves
episodes.plot: Mordecai plans to kiss Margaret at meteor shower to prove to Rigby that he isn't in the "friend zone".

episodes.title: Family BBQ
episodes.plot: When Mordecai is invited to a BBQ with Margaret's family, he tries to get her father to give him a handshake.

episodes.title: The Last Laserdisc Player
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to find a laserdisc player so they can see the director's cut of a famous cult classic.

episodes.title: Country Club
episodes.plot: Mordecai and Rigby try to take back the cart when it is stolen by a rich, snobby country club.

episodes.title: Blind Trust
episodes.plot: Benson has to trust Mordecai and Rigby.

episodes.title: World's Best Boss
episodes.plot: The gang wants to give a Benson a "World's Best Boss" mug.

episodes.title: Last Meal
episodes.plot: Muscleman gets the guys to take him to fast food joints so he can binge on his favorite foods one last time before going on a couple-diet with Starla.

episodes.title: Sleep Fighter
episodes.plot: The gang has to stop Muscleman from fighting in his sleep by finding the source of his nightmares.

episodes.title: Party Re-Pete
episodes.plot: The gang tries to save Benson from an evil party company, who kidnaps and clones to sell their party-animal counterparts.

episodes.title: Steak Me Amadeus
episodes.plot: Mordecai plans to take Margaret out to a fancy restaurant so he can ask her to officially be his girlfriend.
